{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"NetworkInformation","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/NetworkInformation","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","browserCompat":["api.NetworkInformation"],"baseline":{"baseline":false,"support":{"chrome":"67","chrome_android":"67"}},"sidebarHTML":"<ol><li class=\"section\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Network_Information_API\">Network Information API</a></li><li class=\"section\"><em><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/NetworkInformation\" aria-current=\"page\"><code>NetworkInformation</code></a></em></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Instance properties</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/NetworkInformation/downlink\"><code>downlink</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/NetworkInformation/downlinkMax\"><code>downlinkMax</code></a><abbr class=\"icon icon-experimental\" title=\"Experimental. Expect behavior to change in the future.\">\n    <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Experimental</span>\n</abbr></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/NetworkInformation/effectiveType\"><code>effectiveType</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/NetworkInformation/rtt\"><code>rtt</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/NetworkInformation/saveData\"><code>saveData</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/NetworkInformation/type\"><code>type</code></a><abbr class=\"icon icon-experimental\" title=\"Experimental. Expect behavior to change in the future.\">\n    <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Experimental</span>\n</abbr></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Events</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/NetworkInformation/change_event\"><code>change</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Inheritance</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/EventTarget\"><code>EventTarget</code></a></li></ol></details></li><li class=\"toggle\"><details open=\"\"><summary>Related pages for Network Information API</summary><ol><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/connection\"><code>Navigator.connection</code></a></li><li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WorkerNavigator/connection\"><code>WorkerNavigator.connection</code></a></li></ol></details></li></ol>","sidebarMacro":"APIRef","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"notecard note\">\n  <p><strong>Note:</strong> This feature is available in <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Web_Workers_API\">Web Workers</a>.</p>\n</div>\n<p>\n  The <strong><code>NetworkInformation</code></strong> interface of the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Network_Information_API\">Network Information API</a> provides information about the connection a device is using to communicate with the network and provides a means for scripts to be notified if the connection type changes.\n  The <code>NetworkInformation</code> interface cannot be instantiated. It is instead accessed through the <code>connection</code> property of the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator\"><code>Navigator</code></a> interface or the <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/WorkerNavigator\"><code>WorkerNavigator</code></a> interface.\n</p><svg viewBox=\"-1 -1 650 42\" preserveAspectRatio=\"xMinYMin meet\">\n  <a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/EventTarget\">\n    <rect x=\"0\" y=\"0\" width=\"88\" height=\"25\" fill=\"#fff\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" stroke-width=\"2px\"></rect>\n    <text x=\"44\" y=\"16\" font-size=\"10px\" fill=\"#4D4E53\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\n      EventTarget\n    </text>\n  </a>\n  <line x1=\"88\" y1=\"14\" x2=\"118\" y2=\"14\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\"></line>\n  <polyline points=\"88,14 98,9 98,19 88,14\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" fill=\"#fff\"></polyline>\n  <a style=\"text-decoration: none;\" href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/NetworkInformation\" aria-current=\"page\">\n    <rect x=\"118\" y=\"0\" width=\"144\" height=\"25\" fill=\"#F4F7F8\" stroke=\"#D4DDE4\" stroke-width=\"2px\"></rect>\n    <text x=\"190\" y=\"16\" font-size=\"10px\" fill=\"#4D4E53\" text-anchor=\"middle\">\n      NetworkInformation\n    </text>\n  </a></svg>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"instance_properties","title":"Instance properties","isH3":false,"content":"<p><em>This interface also inherits properties of its parent, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/EventTarget\"><code>EventTarget</code></a>.</em></p>\n<dl>\n  <dt id=\"networkinformation.downlink\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/NetworkInformation/downlink\"><code>NetworkInformation.downlink</code></a> <span class=\"badge inline readonly\" title=\"This value may not be changed.\">Read only </span></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Returns the effective bandwidth estimate in megabits per second, rounded to the nearest multiple of 25 kilobits per seconds.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"networkinformation.downlinkmax\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/NetworkInformation/downlinkMax\"><code>NetworkInformation.downlinkMax</code></a> <span class=\"badge inline readonly\" title=\"This value may not be changed.\">Read only </span> <abbr class=\"icon icon-experimental\" title=\"Experimental. Expect behavior to change in the future.\">\n    <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Experimental</span>\n</abbr></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Returns the maximum downlink speed, in megabits per second (Mbps), for the underlying connection technology.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"networkinformation.effectivetype\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/NetworkInformation/effectiveType\"><code>NetworkInformation.effectiveType</code></a> <span class=\"badge inline readonly\" title=\"This value may not be changed.\">Read only </span></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Returns the effective type of the connection meaning one of 'slow-2g', '2g', '3g', or '4g'. This value is determined using a combination of recently observed round-trip time and downlink values.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"networkinformation.rtt\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/NetworkInformation/rtt\"><code>NetworkInformation.rtt</code></a> <span class=\"badge inline readonly\" title=\"This value may not be changed.\">Read only </span></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Returns the estimated effective round-trip time of the current connection, rounded to the nearest multiple of 25 milliseconds.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"networkinformation.savedata\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/NetworkInformation/saveData\"><code>NetworkInformation.saveData</code></a> <span class=\"badge inline readonly\" title=\"This value may not be changed.\">Read only </span></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Returns <code>true</code> if the user has set a reduced data usage option on the user agent.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"networkinformation.type\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/NetworkInformation/type\"><code>NetworkInformation.type</code></a> <span class=\"badge inline readonly\" title=\"This value may not be changed.\">Read only </span> <abbr class=\"icon icon-experimental\" title=\"Experimental. Expect behavior to change in the future.\">\n    <span class=\"visually-hidden\">Experimental</span>\n</abbr></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Returns the type of connection a device is using to communicate with the network. It will be one of the following values:</p>\n    <ul>\n      <li><code>bluetooth</code></li>\n      <li><code>cellular</code></li>\n      <li><code>ethernet</code></li>\n      <li><code>none</code></li>\n      <li><code>wifi</code></li>\n      <li><code>wimax</code></li>\n      <li><code>other</code></li>\n      <li><code>unknown</code></li>\n    </ul>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"instance_methods","title":"Instance methods","isH3":false,"content":"<p><em>This interface also inherits methods of its parent, <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/EventTarget\"><code>EventTarget</code></a>.</em></p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"events","title":"Events","isH3":false,"content":"<dl>\n  <dt id=\"change\"><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/NetworkInformation/change_event\" title=\"change\"><code>change</code></a></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>The event that's fired when connection information changes.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"specifications","value":{"title":"Specifications","id":"specifications","isH3":false,"specifications":[{"bcdSpecificationURL":"https://wicg.github.io/netinfo/#networkinformation-interface","title":"Network Information API"}],"query":"api.NetworkInformation"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"query":"api.NetworkInformation"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/API/Navigator/onLine\">Online and offline events</a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Instance properties","id":"instance_properties"},{"text":"Instance methods","id":"instance_methods"},{"text":"Events","id":"events"},{"text":"Specifications","id":"specifications"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The NetworkInformation interface of the Network Information API provides information about the connection a device is using to communicate with the network and provides a means for scripts to be notified if the connection type changes.\n  The NetworkInformation interface cannot be instantiated. It is instead accessed through the connection property of the Navigator interface or the WorkerNavigator interface.","popularity":0.0075,"modified":"2020-10-15T21:24:38.358Z","other_translations":[],"pageType":"web-api-interface","source":{"folder":"en-us/web/api/networkinformation","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/main/files/en-us/web/api/networkinformation/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/null","filename":"index.md"},"short_title":"NetworkInformation","parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"References"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API","title":"Web APIs"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/NetworkInformation","title":"NetworkInformation"}],"pageTitle":"NetworkInformation - Web APIs | MDN","noIndexing":false},"url":"/en-US/docs/Web/API/NetworkInformation"}